# Line endings are pinned here rather than left to each developer's core.autocrlf.
#
# .editorconfig sets end_of_line = crlf, and dotnet format enforces it against the
# working tree. Without an explicit eol setting a Linux checkout (notably the
# ubuntu-latest runner in .github/workflows/deploy-to-azure.yml) produces LF files,
# so a `dotnet format whitespace --verify-no-changes` gate would fail on every file.
# Pinning eol=crlf keeps the working tree consistent with .editorconfig everywhere
# while still storing normalised LF in the repository.
* text=auto eol=crlf

# Shell scripts must keep LF or they will not execute on Linux. There are none in
# the tree today; this is here so adding one later does not silently break it.
*.sh text eol=lf
